v></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/kVd3e22</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mgxr44]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>100% transparency</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YCo2BxJ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qQ2rdx4.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I’m not usually this honest with you all, but here we go. I know I’ve spent the last two weeks being all excited for mama Bobbie to give birth, and that I took a week off of work to be here for it, and I skipped my trip to Guatemala, but it was not a thing where I want to cuddle with cute little newborns and get cute pics and videos. I’m just scared. I’m really, really scared. 

Mama Sky’s birth was super traumatic for me. It was five hours of pulling kittens out of her and ripping their sacks and clearing their mouths and rubbing their chests to get them breathing. And then keeping them warm and putting them with mama. And then five of the six kittens died anyways. 

This desire to be here with mama Bobbie during her birthing process is not because I want cute kittens to snuggle with. It’s because I want these kittens to stay ALIVE and I feel like if I’m here, they WILL stay alive.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5kTLOqw.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Forgive my honesty. There’s no reason to think that mama Bobbie won’t be the perfect mom. And have a flawless birth. But I have major PTSD from the last black cat to give birth on my kitten room mattress. 

I have full faith in Bobbie. She survived a dog attack while pregnant like a BAD ASS and is still super sweet and affectionate. I love her so much and I know she will be a great mama. But any and all good thoughts and vibes you can send this way are much appreciated</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YCo2BxJ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[KittensForDays]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Cat!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zQwiYRv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/N9MXTD8.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/zQwiYRv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SkyPigeon123]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>How Not to Information Security</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Fht784j</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mnVuMCq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is an example of how information and operational security is very important and should be paid attention to.

